Then, at the blink of an eye, the sky opened up, and an eerie purple color flooded the sky.  The West Commonlands was caught in a torrential downpour, and as animals hid under trees, guards ran into their booth, and other adventurers sought shelter in the cave into Befallen, I welcomed the water with open arms.  I stripped my robe off of my frail body, and in the middle of a wide-open field, let the rain nourish my skin with its healing power.  A soft glow overcame my body, and I began to feel my pours absorb the power of this water.  I began to feel rejuvenated, and with a shriek yell that rang through the trees, I silenced the water, and the golden sun appeared again.  Refreshed, I continued my journey...<br>
