ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Karnors Castle</span><hr size=1> Ahh my poor gnomish friend, I read your tale and feel your pain.  Your tale has peaked my interest and an overwhelming desire has overtaken me to come back and read your journal as it progresses.  I too have seen the carnage you have encountered... and I have come to the aid of those who have been vanquished,  if I can attend to them in time. It has been known that I have almost perfected the ability to reunite a soul with it's shell of flesh, although this is a tricky matter.   The soul and flesh only have a short time before they forget they were once a pair.  I must administer my aid quickly before all is lost.  And yet this ressurection of a soul and body is not without some cost.  Warriors, beastlords, enchanters and others all tell the tale of some lost memories once they are reunited, they tell of a sickness and weakness that passes over time.  But alas, even with these costs, it is a small price to pay for a task so daunting.  I wish you good journeys my friend and if our paths cross along the way and I can be of service to you in your search for the enemy you seek, please seek me out to aid your journey.  The gnomes of Ak'Anon have long been my friends and it pains me to see one of their fold die so horribly.<br>
