I continue my journey to North Freeport, but now my reasons for traveling are selfless.  I click the hells of my journeysman boots together, and it creates a shiny white cloud of sparkles, and my step hastens.  Halfway to my destination, I see a halfling sitting underneath the shade of a tree, using a dagger to cut pieces of his apple held in his hand.  Knowing halflings are inquisitive by nature, I decided to stop and ask if he has seen this necromancer named Aarathin.  As I posed the question, the dagger fell from his hand, nearly missing his hairy feet before digging its point into a root.  He looks up at me with wandering eyes, his mouth half-full of chewed apple.  He tells me he saw a skeleton scatter by about 30 minutes ago, although it was not an ordinary skeleton.  &quot;His bones were covered with small, dull bumps, and was partially covered in a fungus.  Death danced in his eye sockets, and looked as if he could give you a terrible plague at the point of a finger.&quot; I asked which direction he was traveling, and the halfling pointed north towards Nektulos Forest.  I summoned him a firework for his cooperation, and he seemed content.  Continuing on, I proceeded to Nektulos, to what may very well be my death... <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=291365</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ciniminiteenytiny>Cinimini Teenytiny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Master</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/13/02 8:40:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Nektulos Forest</span><hr size=1>      Diseased corpses scattered the ground as I continued my journey.  It was as if this necromancer knew of my presence and hunt, and was leading me to him.  The decay, to my surprise, lead me not to North Freeport, but instead north to Nektulos Forest.  A chill shot down my spine at the thought of entering the dark forest.  I knew the trees were inhabited by the Dark Elves, and although at 59 seasons I was far superior to them individually, they flocked in hordes and were quick to draw their cold steel blades against my neck.  This was indeed no place for a gnome.<br>
     Cautiously I stepped into the forest, my Apothic Boots crushed the pebbles and sticks beneath my feet.  I grasped my Chetari Wardstaff tightly, and watched every blown leaf with a careful eye.  An eerie mist entangled my legs, and made it impossible to even see the ground which was 3 feet from my eyes.  Step by step I found, myself lost within the forest within minutes.  Agonizing screams and howls flooded my ears, to the point where I felt my blood become warm.  The screams must lead to Aarathin, I thought, and timidly followed the call.<br>
